{"parentUuid":"0dab8fc9-956e-4028-b2d7-157521d8f943","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_012ciiVjCziQQB5aDL1tL9kP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"","signature":""}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4574,"cache_read_input_tokens":82250,"output_tokens":5076,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4574,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":5076,"cache_read_input_tokens":82250,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4574,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4574},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcMxi1Bk855XMUdpz2Bk1","type":"assistant","uuid":"19d6a9be-6505-4416-b090-1c6d2648af2e","timestamp":"2026-06-24T10:55:21.059Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/gotha/Projects/github.com/gotha/dotfiles","sessionId":"108e6e67-96cc-4dca-bc52-61b8eb2c1144","version":"2.1.175","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"19d6a9be-6505-4416-b090-1c6d2648af2e","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_012ciiVjCziQQB5aDL1tL9kP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Confirmed — full diagnosis below.\n\n## What's breaking the permissions\n\nIt's **not** the container or anything external touching the data — it's a `systemd-tmpfiles` rule shipped by the *deployed* version of your luna-podcatcher NixOS module:\n\n```\nd '/var/lib/luna-podcatcher/pgdata' 0700 root root - -\n```\n\nThis rule forces the bind-mounted PGDATA directory to **`root:root`, mode `0700`**. The containerized postgres runs as **uid 70** (Alpine's `postgres` user). A `0700` dir owned by root can't be *entered* by uid 70, so postgres gets \"Permission denied\" on everything inside it — exactly the errors in the log (`global/pg_filenode.map`, `pg_logical/snapshots`, `postmaster.pid`).\n\nThe exact timeline from this boot proves it:\n\n| time (local) | event |\n|---|---|\n| 13:26:47 | container starts; postgres entrypoint chowns PGDATA → `70:70`, works fine ✓ |\n| **13:31:18** | systemd runs *\"Re-setup tmpfiles on a system that is already running\"* → re-applies the rule → PGDATA reset to **`root:root 0700`** |\n| 13:31:49 | postgres's first 5‑min checkpoint tries to enter PGDATA → **Permission denied** ✗ |\n\nYour `chown -R 70:70` undoes it — until the next reboot (or any tmpfiles re-setup) re-applies the rule. That's why it comes back every restart.\n\n## Why it persists (and the good news)\n\nYou **already fixed this** in the luna-podcatcher repo. Compare:\n\n- **Deployed rev `f27ac85`** (what's running) emits the bad rule: `++ optional useContainer \"d '...pgdata' 0700 root root - -\"`.\n- **Current repo HEAD `b7c3f97`** removed it, with a comment that nails the exact bug: *\"a tmpfiles rule would re-chown it to root on every rebuild and break the database with 'permission denied' on its files.\"*\n\nThe problem is `flake.lock` in your dotfiles still pins luna-podcatcher to the orphaned old rev `f27ac85` (it was rewritten into `91d6b21`, which is *not* an ancestor of the lock). So the system keeps building the buggy module.\n\n## How to fix it\n\nRe-lock to your repo's current HEAD and rebuild — the bad rule disappears:\n\n```bash\ncd ~/Projects/github.com/gotha/dotfiles\nnix flake update luna-podcatcher        # relock to b7c3f97 (has the fix)\nsudo nixos-rebuild switch --flake .#lucie\n```\n\nAfter the rebuild, tmpfiles no longer manages PGDATA, so your manual `chown` becomes permanent. To be safe, restart the container once so postgres clears its degraded state:\n\n```bash\nsudo chown -R 70:70 /var/lib/luna-podcatcher/pgdata   # if not already correct\nsudo systemctl restart docker-luna-podcatcher-db\n```\n\n(No emergency right now — PGDATA is currently `70:70` and `pg_isready` reports accepting connections; it recovered after your last chown.)\n\nWant me to run the `nix flake update` + `nixos-rebuild switch` for you? The flake update is harmless (only rewrites `flake.lock`, which is already dirty); the rebuild is reversible via NixOS generations but will need your sudo password."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4574,"cache_read_input_tokens":82250,"output_tokens":5076,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4574,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":5076,"cache_read_input_tokens":82250,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4574,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4574},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcMxi1Bk855XMUdpz2Bk1","type":"assistant","uuid":"c67f0811-fc1e-4775-9b1e-23e3b0932dfc","timestamp":"2026-06-24T10:55:34.266Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","c